  "body": "***Type***: Bug\r\n\r\n***Summary***: Let's take there are C1 (Sender) and C2 (Recipient). In many cases, 'Sender' may start 1-1 chat with the Recipient while the last is **offline** or **online but use different network** than Client. \r\nIn any of that cases - Recipient will never see messages (and 1-1 chat never appears) from the Sender even if both appear online on the same network and Sender sends messages again and again. \r\n\r\nNeither 1-1 chat created nor messages received by the recipient if message sender starts the chat while recipient in a different network or offline.\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n1-1 chat created and messages arrive to the recipient after he appears online in the same network 1-1 chat has been created in. \r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nMessages never reach recipient if contact added while being offline (or being on a different network)\r\n\r\n### Reproduction 1\r\n- Open Status on the Device1 and the Device2\r\n- Create an account on Device1 and switch to 'Mainnet with upstream RPC' network (Contact1)\r\n- Create an account on Device2 and switch to 'Ropsten with upstream RPC' network (Contact2)\r\n- Contact1 adds Contact2 in contacts (doesn't matter via QR code scan or public key submit)\r\n- Contact1 sends a message\r\n- Contact2 switch the network to 'Mainnet with upstream RPC'\r\n- Contact2 logs in to account and stays on the Home screen\r\n- (Optional) Contact1 sends a message again \r\n\r\n### Reproduction 2\r\n- Open Status on the Device1 and the Device2\r\n- Create Contact1 and Contact2 respectively\r\n- Keep public key (or QR contact code) of the Contact2\r\n- Contact2 logs out\r\n- Contact1 adds Contact2 in contacts (doesn't matter via QR code scan or public key submit)\r\n- Contact2 logs in to account and stays on the Home screen\r\n- (Optional) Contact1 sends a message again \r\n\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n* Status version: Develop (354th build) and release 0.9.17\r\n* Operating System: Android and iOS\r\n\r\n#### Logs\r\nBelow two sessions reflecting Reproduction 1 (changing network) above:\r\nTF session with logs for Sender side: https://app.testfairy.com/projects/4803590-status/builds/8168269/sessions/25/?accessToken=hjkpX71pGqAuXG8Wk229cmciV9I\r\nTF session with logs for Recipient side: https://app.testfairy.com/projects/4803622-status/builds/8167404/sessions/83/?accessToken=k4UIGu9qIjkTmCJKbx8e3Ige10Y\n\n<blockquote><div><strong><a href=\"https://app.testfairy.com/projects/4803590-status/builds/8168269/sessions/25/?accessToken=hjkpX71pGqAuXG8Wk229cmciV9I\">TestFairy: Status 0.9.17 (2458) @25</a></strong></div></blockquote>\n<blockquote><div><strong><a href=\"https://app.testfairy.com/projects/4803622-status/builds/8167404/sessions/83/?accessToken=k4UIGu9qIjkTmCJKbx8e3Ige10Y\">TestFairy: Status 0.9.16-31-ga7bd6b6e+ (2458) @83</a></strong></div></blockquote>",
